ViPragSent Private Research Use Terms
Version 1.0, 16 July 2026

Copyright (c) 2026 Lê Minh Hiếu. All rights reserved.

1. Scope

These terms apply only to original code, documentation, annotations, experiment
configurations, evaluation outputs, and model modifications created by the
ViPragSent project (the "Project Materials"). They do not grant rights to any
third-party material, including source social-media text, the ViSoBERT export,
external evaluation datasets, or base-model weights.

2. Permitted use

The copyright holder permits authorized project collaborators and confidential
academic peer reviewers to access and use the Project Materials solely for
private, non-commercial research, verification, and reproduction of the
ViPragSent experiments.

3. Restrictions

Unless the copyright holder gives prior written permission, recipients may not:

  a. publish, sublicense, sell, redistribute, or make the Project Materials or
     any raw social-media text available to third parties;
  b. use the Project Materials for commercial, production, surveillance,
     profiling, or other high-impact automated decision-making purposes;
  c. attempt to identify or contact individuals represented in the data;
  d. remove copyright, provenance, privacy, or third-party notices; or
  e. represent generated rationales or model outputs as human-verified facts.

4. Data and third-party rights

No license to redistribute raw ViPragSent text is granted. Access to the local
ViSoBERT export is limited to private research while its source terms are being
confirmed. UIT-VSFC, UIT-VSMEC, and AIVIVN are external evaluation benchmarks,
not components of ViPragSent, and remain governed by their respective terms.

PhoBERT, XLM-R, Sailor-7B, Vistral-7B, and all other base models remain governed
by their respective licenses and access conditions. Project checkpoints and
adapters do not include or relicense base-model weights.

5. Publication

Aggregate statistics, metrics, tables, figures, and methodological descriptions
may be included in an academic paper provided that they do not disclose raw
restricted text, personal information, credentials, or third-party materials.

6. Termination

Permission terminates automatically upon breach of these terms. On termination,
the recipient must stop using and delete all copies of restricted Project
Materials, except copies retained solely where required by law.

7. Disclaimer

THE PROJECT MATERIALS ARE PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND,
EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A
PARTICULAR PURPOSE, NON-INFRINGEMENT, OR ACCURACY. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE
COPYRIGHT HOLDER BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY ARISING
FROM THE PROJECT MATERIALS OR THEIR USE.

These terms document the project's private-research access policy and are not a
substitute for permission from third-party rights holders.
